<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1242,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1576195181" country="Namibia" county="It" location="Kamaggas" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="Northern Cape" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1242,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Comments.</emphasis>
As in the previous species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[616,770,1244,1267]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tersissima">
<emphasis box="[616,770,1244,1267]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. tersissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1061,1159,1242,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">holotype</typeStatus>
and a single taxonomic entry. 
<collectingCounty box="[221,238,1279,1302]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">It</collectingCounty>
was described based on the male from &quot; 
<collectingMunicipality box="[689,911,1278,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Petit Namaqualand</collectingMunicipality>
: 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF20C6FB533C6FFAFD" box="[922,1043,1279,1303]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Kamaggas" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">Kamaggas</location>
&quot; (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1151,1278,1303]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="7.[151,250,944,966]" captionTargetBox="[162,1418,195,922]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 30. Distribution records of Afrotropical Micaria: M. beaufortia (circle), M. chrysis (square) and M. tersissima (diamond)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832830/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF27CFFB523C9AFAFD" box="[1171,1254,1278,1303]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Similar" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">Similar</location>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1289,1406,1278,1303]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micariolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysis">
<emphasis box="[1289,1406,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. chrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is currently listed in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF22EFFA8E3AD7FAD1" box="[435,683,1314,1339]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="World Spider Catalog" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">World Spider Catalog</location>
(2017) as being known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1030,1129,1314,1339]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Namibia</collectingCountry>
, although it was described from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF2385FAEA39B7FAB5" box="[217,459,1350,1375]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="South Africa. Simon" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">
South Africa. 
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[386,459,1350,1375]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Simon, E. (1910) Arachnoidea. Araneae (ii). In: Schultze, L. (Ed.), Zoologische und anthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im Westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Denkschriften der Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 1910, pp. 175 - 218." type="journal article" year="1910">Simon</bibRefCitation>
</location>
(1910) mentioned that the species certainly belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westring" authorityYear="1851" box="[1125,1215,1351,1374]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1125,1215,1351,1374]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Micaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and indicated the presence of a small thoracic fovea (as an exceptional character). A small fovea is present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tucker" authorityYear="1923" box="[1189,1344,1386,1411]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beaufortia">
<emphasis box="[1189,1344,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. beaufortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1360,1427,1386,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ‒ 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1636,1659]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 ‒ 7. Habitus, legs and male palp of Micaria beaufortia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832820/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and also documented in 
<taxonomicName authority="Sundevall, 1831" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1831" box="[442,820,1422,1447]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicaria">
<emphasis box="[442,604,1423,1447]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. formicaria</emphasis>
(Sundevall, 1831)
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 4a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich" box="[962,1165,1422,1447]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" refString="Wunderlich, J. (1980) Revision der europaischen Arten der Gattung Micaria Westring 1851, mit Anmerkungen zu den ubrigen palaarktischen Arten (Arachnida: Araneida: Gnaphosidae). Zoologische Beitrage, 25 (1979), 233 - 341." type="journal article" year="1980">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF209EFA223C39FA4D" box="[962,1093,1422,1447]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Wunderlich" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">Wunderlich</location>
1980
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF27F9FA233CCAFA4C" box="[1189,1206,1423,1446]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="It" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">It</location>
is unlikely that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tersissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. tersissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tucker" authorityYear="1923" box="[320,476,1458,1483]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beaufortia">
<emphasis box="[320,343,1460,1483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[359,476,1458,1483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">beaufortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are conspecific; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[668,821,1460,1483]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tersissima">
<emphasis box="[668,821,1460,1483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. tersissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males are smaller, only 
<quantity box="[1097,1184,1458,1483]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long vs. 4.35 long for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tucker" authorityYear="1923" box="[151,309,1494,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Micaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beaufortia">
<emphasis box="[151,309,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">M. beaufortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F832A659FFFAFFEF23CBFBFC3B91F9F9:75444194FFFAFFEF2215FA7A39DEFA05" box="[329,418,1494,1519]" country="Namibia" county="It" municipality="Petit Namaqualand" name="Judging" pageId="1" pageNumber="463" stateProvince="Northern Cape">Judging</location>
from their similar size and closely spaced 
<typeStatus box="[938,986,1495,1519]" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">type</typeStatus>
localities, these two species from the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,317,1530,1555]" country="South Africa" name="Northern Cape" pageId="1" pageNumber="463">Northern Cape</collectingRegion>
and known by different sexes might end up being synonyms.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
